/r9k/ is an imageboard where there are no exact reposts.

1. If you attempt to post something unoriginal, it is not posted, and you are muted temporarily.
2. The time with which you are muted for doubles with each transgression.
3. Each mute time is 2^n in seconds where n is the number of times you have transgressed. So, your mute time doubles each time you fuck up.
4. Backlinks, eg >>1, are not viewed by the robot. So "lolwut" and ">>2 lolwut" are the same post, in the eyes of the robot.
5. Gibberish at the end of a post to force originality may result in mod intervention (no BLOX posts please).
6. Images are NOT included in the filter, only text.
7. Your mute count slowly decreases over time.
8. You cannot post a picture without text.
9. Unicode is blocked. Sorry, too many exploits (Cyrillic letters, etc).
10. Posts require a certain minimum amount of original content in order to be posted.
11. Post sane, real content, well thought out replies, and mutes are unlikely.
12. The original algorithm was designed by XKCD:
http://blag.xkcd.com/2008/01/14/robot9000-and-xkcd-signal-attacking-noise-in-chat/

>Does anyone else ever get the "what the hell am I doing with my life?" type of feelings out of the blue?
Every moment of every day, there's never an hour where I'm not struck by some existential crisis and left contemplating everything that's lead up to this point. But here's the thing, it's always been like this. Ever since childhood I've been immersed in some sort of intensive daydream or another and he's not the first fictional character I've fallen in love with. This is life for me and will always be in someway.

But unlike every other fictional fixation or suitor I had, for who I wasted time away in fantasy worlds for and neglected myself and my responsibilities - I was going to treat *him* very fucking differently. It was a promise I made to myself. I had to prove to myself that I could be a waifufag and productive at the same time. I was going to lose thirty pounds (done) and gut my depression room (done) and start lifting (a little more everyday) and get my garden started (in the works) and a few other more subtle or social things in my everyday life.

These might be small accomplishments to some and none change the fact that I'm still an autistic outcast woman in love with Doomguy whose grip on reality isn't that firm, but it's a start that changed my entire world, a huge revelation that I have control over my own mind (which ironically is like... his entire shtick kek) and paved the way for me to set larger goals in the future.

You can too, anon. Turn all of those feelings of love and devotion outwards into the real world, not inwards into fantasy. It doesn't have to be some grand self-improver meme transformation, it only has to be enough to impress yourself.
